THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 236 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 to 5, inclusive, of this
3 act.
4 Sec. 2. 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim the
5 fifteenth day of the eighth month of the Hindu calendar to be
6 “Diwali Day” in the State of Nevada.
7 2. The proclamation may call upon the news media,
8 educators, business and labor leaders and appropriate
9 governmental officers to bring to the attention of the residents of
10 Nevada the diversity and inclusion of the cultures that celebrate
11 Diwali in the State of Nevada and throughout the world.
12 Sec. 3. 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim the first
13 day of the tenth month of the Islamic calendar to be “Eid al-Fitr
14 Day” in the State of Nevada.
15 2. The proclamation may call upon the news media,
16 educators, business and labor leaders and appropriate
17 governmental officers to bring to the attention of the residents of
18 Nevada the diversity and inclusion of the cultures that celebrate
19 Eid al-Fitr in the State of Nevada and throughout the world.
20 Sec. 4. 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim the first
21 day of the month of Vaisakh of the Sikh calendar to be “Vaisakhi
22 Day” in the State of Nevada.
23 2. The proclamation may call upon the news media,
24 educators, business and labor leaders and appropriate
25 governmental officers to bring to the attention of the residents of
26 Nevada the diversity and inclusion of the cultures that celebrate
27 Vaisakhi in the State of Nevada and throughout the world.
28 Sec. 5. 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim the day of
29 the first full moon in the month of May to be “Vesak Day,” also
30 known as “Buddha Day,” in the State of Nevada.
31 2. The proclamation may call upon the news media,
32 educators, business and labor leaders and appropriate
33 governmental officers to bring to the attention of the residents of
34 Nevada the diversity and inclusion of the cultures that celebrate
35 Vesak in the State of Nevada and throughout the world.
36 Sec. 6. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.
